# .trivyignore - Suppress CVEs that cannot be fixed by the application
#
# These CVEs are in packages VENDORED INSIDE setuptools (setuptools/_vendor/).
# They are not directly installable or controllable via requirements.txt.
# The fix requires a newer setuptools release baked into the base Docker image.
#
# CVE-2026-23949: jaraco.context vendored in setuptools 79.0.1; fixed in setuptools >= TBD
CVE-2026-23949
#
# CVE-2026-24049: wheel vendored in setuptools 79.0.1; fixed in setuptools >= TBD
CVE-2026-24049
#
# CVE-2026-24486: python-multipart path traversal; fix version (0.0.22) not yet published on PyPI
# Remove this entry once 0.0.22 is released and requirements.txt is updated
CVE-2026-24486

# CVE-2026-0861: glibc vulnerability in base Debian image; no fix available yet
CVE-2026-0861
